The Constitutional Court has declared a section of the Electoral Act as unconstitutional. This paves the way for independent candidates to contest provincial and national elections. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - In a landmark judgment,Â the Constitutional Court has declared a section of the Electoral Act as unconstitutional. The judgment means that independent candidates may now run in provincial and national elections. Political parties were only allowed to contest polls provincially and nationally. READ: Judgment reserved in tobacco case Independent candidates were only permitted to contest for local government. NGO New Nation Movement wanted the electoral act to be amended to allow independent candidates to run in provincial and national elections. The Electoral Act has been declared unconstitutional for not allowing individuals to stand for election. eNCA reporter Lindokuhle Xulu is following that case for us. Courtesy #DStv403